Bank of Japan Current-Account Deposits Set to Climb to Record $537 Billion

-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 
2011-03-22T00:11:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/bank-of-japan-current-account-deposits-set-to-climb-to-record-537-billion.html
The outstanding current account
deposits held by private financial institutions at the  Bank of
Japan (8301)  is projected to climb to a record 43.6 trillion yen ($537
billion), the central bank said. The Bank of  Japan  added 2
trillion yen today in a one-day operation.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Naoto Hosoda at 
 nhosoda@bloomberg.net  